title: Revolutionary America, 1763-1815 A Political History
description: Revolutionary America, 1763-1815 examines the crucial events in the history of the United States during this period. Placing the political revolution at the core of the story, the book considers the deterioration of relations between Britain and the colonists, the Wars of Independence, the creation of the republican government, the ratification of the U.S. Constitution, and the challenges of the republic's early years.
